About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. ‚ÄúAlpha‚Äù, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.

About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. ‚ÄúAlpha‚Äù, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.

snippet.title: INDIA vs ENGLAND, 5th Test Final Day Live Commentary | IND vs ENG, Test Live Match Today | Last Inng
snippet.description:
#cricketlive #cricketmatch #indvsseng 

INDIA vs ENGLAND, 5th Test Final Day Live Commentary | IND vs ENG, Test Live Match Today | Last Inng

INDIA VS ENGALND Test 5 Day 4 Preview :

England need 324 more runs to win the match and the series, while India are effectively eight wickets away from leveling the series 2-2 (assuming Woakes won‚Äôt come out to bat).

With England 233/6, needing 35 more to win, and India just four wickets away from a series-levelling triumph, bad light and rain brought an early end to a gripping day. Chris Woakes was seen padded up in his whites yesterday, hinting he could bat today if needed despite the shoulder injury.

The final day promises high drama‚Äîwill India snatch victory, can England hold their nerve, or will we witness a once-in-a-generation tie? Don‚Äôt blink. Every ball today could decide the series!


Early stumps on Day 4 due to a wet outfield. England need just 35 runs; India need 4 wickets (assuming Chris Woakes comes out to bat). Boos ring around the ground, but like the previous four matches in this series, the final Test will also head into a fifth day. 

The day started well for the visitors as they knocked over Ben Dukett and Ollie Pope in quick succession to push the hosts on the back foot. England were 106 for three at one stage and needed 268 runs to win. 

Joe Root and Harry Brook then played out of their skins and put on a stunning partnership of 195 runs for the fourth wicket.

Brook was on 19 when he gave India an opportunity but Mohammed Siraj, at deep backward square leg, took the catch and stepped on the boundary cushions. That triggered something in Brook and he unleashed his fury on the Indian bowlers.

In a bid to get quick runs, Brook miscued one to Siraj, who managed to hold onto it and ended his knock at 111. 

Root was steady as he brought up his 39th Test hundred. However, trying to steer one to third man, he edged the ball straight to the keeper. 


India (Probable XI): Yashasvi Jaiswal, KL Rahul, B Sai Sudharsan, Shubman Gill (c), Ravindra Jadeja, Dhruv Jurel (wk), Washington Sundar, Shardul Thakur/Arshdeep Singh, Akash Deep, Mohammed Siraj, Jasprit Bumrah/Prasidh Krishna


England Playing XI: Zak Crawley, Ben Duckett, Ollie Pope (c), Joe Root, Harry Brook, Jacob Bethell, Jamie Smith (wk), Jamie Overton, Chris Woakes, Gus Atkinson, Josh Tongue

snippet.title: COOLIE Trailer Reaction! | Rajinikanth | Nagarjuna Akkineni | Aamir Khan
snippet.description:
Jaby & Achara react to the explosive trailer for Coolie, marking the fiery return of Rajinikanth in a mass-loaded, emotional action drama.

Directed by Lokesh Kanagaraj (Leo, Vikram), Coolie brings back Rajinikanth (Jailer, Kaala) in a powerful new avatar‚Äîmixing grit, style, and legacy. With Anirudh Ravichander‚Äôs pulse-pounding score and stunning visuals, the film promises high-octane action and deep-rooted emotion.

Jaby & Achara break down the intensity, vintage Rajini swag, and Lokesh‚Äôs signature world-building. Coolie looks like a full-blown cinematic celebration of one of India‚Äôs biggest icons.

____________________

snippet.title: The Conjuring: Last Rites | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Discover why this case ended it all. #TheConjuring: Last Rites - Only in Theaters September 5.

From New Line Cinema comes the ninth entry in the more than $2 billion theatrical Conjuring universe, The Conjuring: Last Rites, directed by franchise veteran Michael Chaves and produced by franchise architects James Wan and Peter Safran.

The Conjuring: Last Rites delivers another thrilling chapter of the iconic Conjuring cinematic universe, based on real events.  Vera Farmiga and Patrick Wilson reunite for one last case as renowned, real-life paranormal investigators Ed and Lorraine Warren in a powerful and spine-chilling addition to the global box office-breaking franchise.

Farmiga and Wilson star alongside Mia Tomlinson and Ben Hardy, who portray Ed and Lorraine‚Äôs daughter Judy Warren and her boyfriend, Tony Spera, as well as Steve Coulter returning as Father Gordon, Rebecca Calder, Elliot Cowan, K√≠la Lord Cassidy, Beau Gadsdon, John Brotherton and Shannon Kook.

Chaves directs from a screenplay by Ian Goldberg & Richard Naing and David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, story by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick & James Wan, based on characters created by Chad Hayes & Carey W. Hayes.  The executive producers are Michael Clear, Judson Scott, Hans Ritter, David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, Natalia Safran, John Rickard and Michael Chaves.

Chaves is joined behind the camera by his creative team, including director of photography Eli Born, production designer John Frankish, editors Elliot Greenberg and Gregory Plotkin, visual effects supervisor Scott Edelstein, visual effects producer Eric Bruneau and costume designer Graham Churchyard, with casting by Rose Wicksteed and Sophie Kingston-Smith.  The music supervisor is Ian Broucek and the music is by composer Benjamin Wallfisch.

New Line Cinema Presents The Safran Company / An Atomic Monster Production, The Conjuring: Last Rites.  The film will be released worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures and will be only in theaters and IMAX¬Æ in North America on September 5, 2025, and internationally beginning 3 September 2025.

en.description:
Discover why this case ended it all. #TheConjuring: Last Rites - Only in Theaters September 5.

From New Line Cinema comes the ninth entry in the more than $2 billion theatrical Conjuring universe, The Conjuring: Last Rites, directed by franchise veteran Michael Chaves and produced by franchise architects James Wan and Peter Safran.

The Conjuring: Last Rites delivers another thrilling chapter of the iconic Conjuring cinematic universe, based on real events.  Vera Farmiga and Patrick Wilson reunite for one last case as renowned, real-life paranormal investigators Ed and Lorraine Warren in a powerful and spine-chilling addition to the global box office-breaking franchise.

Farmiga and Wilson star alongside Mia Tomlinson and Ben Hardy, who portray Ed and Lorraine‚Äôs daughter Judy Warren and her boyfriend, Tony Spera, as well as Steve Coulter returning as Father Gordon, Rebecca Calder, Elliot Cowan, K√≠la Lord Cassidy, Beau Gadsdon, John Brotherton and Shannon Kook.

Chaves directs from a screenplay by Ian Goldberg & Richard Naing and David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, story by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick & James Wan, based on characters created by Chad Hayes & Carey W. Hayes.  The executive producers are Michael Clear, Judson Scott, Hans Ritter, David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, Natalia Safran, John Rickard and Michael Chaves.

Chaves is joined behind the camera by his creative team, including director of photography Eli Born, production designer John Frankish, editors Elliot Greenberg and Gregory Plotkin, visual effects supervisor Scott Edelstein, visual effects producer Eric Bruneau and costume designer Graham Churchyard, with casting by Rose Wicksteed and Sophie Kingston-Smith.  The music supervisor is Ian Broucek and the music is by composer Benjamin Wallfisch.

New Line Cinema Presents The Safran Company / An Atomic Monster Production, The Conjuring: Last Rites.  The film will be released worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures and will be only in theaters and IMAX¬Æ in North America on September 5, 2025, and internationally beginning 3 September 2025.

snippet.description:
#AadiPerukku #AmmanSongs #AadiMasam #LREswari #Veeramanidasan #ShakthiShanmugaraja #AmmanBakthi

The album ‚ÄúAadi Perukku - ‡ÆÜ‡Æü‡Æø‡Æ™‡Øç‡Æ™‡ØÜ‡Æ∞‡ØÅ‡Æï‡Øç‡Æï‡ØÅ‚Äù is dedicated to Goddess Amman. This album has 9 songs sung by S.P.B, L.R Eswari, Mahanadhi Shobana, Bombay Saradha, P. Susheela, S. Janaki & Sakthi Dasan
Music By : Kanmani Raja D.V. Ramani, Aravind 
Lyrics By : Mugilan, Bharathi Ganesh
Produced By : Unique Recording

Amman is the South Indian Goddess of Rain. She is the main South Indian mother/goddess in the southern India. Mari is closely associated with the Hindu goddess Parvati and Durga. Her festivals are held during the late summer/early autumn season of Aadi throughout Tamil Nadu and Deccan region, the largest being Aadi Thiruvizha. Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You All ! Om Sakthi !

Do Like, Share, Comment & Subscribe to Amman Bakthi !

The album ‚ÄúAadi Perukku - ‡ÆÜ‡Æü‡Æø‡Æ™‡Øç‡Æ™‡ØÜ‡Æ∞‡ØÅ‡Æï‡Øç‡Æï‡ØÅ‚Äù is dedicated to Goddess Amman. This album has 9 songs sung by S.P.B, L.R Eswari, Mahanadhi Shobana, Bombay Saradha, P. Susheela, S. Janaki & Sakthi Dasan
Music By : Kanmani Raja D.V. Ramani, Aravind 
Lyrics By : Mugilan, Bharathi Ganesh
Produced By : Unique Recording

Amman is the South Indian Goddess of Rain. She is the main South Indian mother/goddess in the southern India. Mari is closely associated with the Hindu goddess Parvati and Durga. Her festivals are held during the late summer/early autumn season of Aadi throughout Tamil Nadu and Deccan region, the largest being Aadi Thiruvizha. Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You All ! Om Sakthi !

snippet.title: [EN] 2025 PMWC at EWC Grand Finals D3 | PUBG MOBILE WORLD CUP at ESPORTS WORLD CUP
snippet.description:
üèÜ GRAND FINALS DAY 3 | AUGUST 3

The stage is set for the epic conclusion of the 2025 PUBG MOBILE WORLD CUP at ESPORTS WORLD CUP! After weeks of breath taking competition, today marks the final day of the Grand Finals in Riyadh, where one team will rise above the rest to claim the crown and secure their place in PUBG MOBILE history.

This is it ‚Äî the last matches of 2025 PMWC at EWC. The world‚Äôs best 16 teams have given everything, but only one will lift the trophy and take home the lion‚Äôs share of the $3,000,000 prize pool. Every rotation, every zone, and every elimination today could change the outcome of the entire championship because, now a team can win with SMASH RULE.

After an unforgettable journey through the Group Stage and the Survival Stage, today we crown the champion of 2025 PMWC at EWC.

üî• How does SMASH RULE work? 
On the last day of the 2025 PMWC Grand Finals, we have the Match Point Threshold! In Overall Ranking after 12th match, #1 ranked team‚Äôs points +10. Any team that hits this must then win a later match to claim the trophy‚Äîwinning the same match where they reach the threshold doesn‚Äôt bring the championship. If no team secures the title via SMASH Rule by Match 18, the team with the highest total points wins under standard rules.

üî• Why You Can‚Äôt Miss 2025 PMWC at EWC:
- The top 16 teams on one stage ‚Äî no second chances!
- Every match counts in the race for the championship!
- Witness PUBG MOBILE history in the making!
- Explosive SMASH RULE format ‚Äî pressure-packed, winner-takes-all action!
